Founded by West Orange citrus families who desired a laid-back, easy going, old south type feel to their club, membership is available to you today.
The combination of facilities, friends, and service is second to none and unique to Central Florida. With memberships currently available, we invite you to take a tour of our website and experience everything the Club has to offer. From Golf to Dining, the West Orange Country Club has activities for the whole family.

$
18 Hole Golf Course
/$
$
Our golf course is located in the heart of Florida. You can play the course seven days a week. The West Orange Country Club golf course is a Lloyd Clifton design built in 1967. Our challenging par 71 course is tree lined with several small ponds and a creek that winds through the property. Rebuilt in 2006 with Tift dwarf grass, the greens are smooth and undulating enough to test the best players in the area. Home of the West Orange Invitational, West Orange welcomes the best amateurs of Central Florida each November. Over the years West Orange has hosted many mini tour events including the Hooters Tour and Suncoast Ladies Series.
​

Safety First Swim School provides survival swim instruction to children ages 6 months and older. Safety First Swim makes your child our first priority. It is for this reason, we conduct our classes in a private setting while giving each family extra time to ask questions and learn about the survival swim skills their child is receiving. Safety First Swim is proud to provide private lessons at the West Orange Country Club. Whether you're searching for infant swimming lessons for your baby or toddler, or swimming lessons for your older child - Discover the Safety First Swim School Difference. Visit
www.safetyfirstswim.com
